22/03/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- NATO Secretary General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer said in a media interview that parliamentary elections in Macedonia later this year would be a key test of the country's bid to become a member of the Pact. In a statement broadcast during the Macedonian-language programme of the Voice of America, de Hoop Scheffer stressed that the vote was expected to be "110 per cent" fair and democratic. Macedonian Prime Minister Vlado Buckovski meets with the NATO chief and senior EU officials in Brussels Wednesday. 
Separately, European Commission President Jose Manuel Barroso also stressed the importance of holding elections in line with European standards, in a letter to Buckovski. (Macedonian Government Web site - 22/03/06; Makfax, NATO Web site - 21/03/06)
